{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"body":"Re-review of the REVISED plan: PASS (0 blocking, 16 advisory) — the deviation (replication.config fix + deployment) is now gated. Triage of the 16 advisories:\n\nFIX IN-SCOPE (S3):\n- [E4/#16] get_change_refspec claim: reword to cite it as EXTERNAL g2p source (lfit/releng-gerrit_to_platform@44d5d46 helpers.py:278-291, research-verified) — it is NOT a local-repo symbol; will fix the wording in the ini/dispatch note.\n- [G6/T5b/#1,#15] Replication-lag race (first patchset on a brand-new feature branch can 422 if workflow_dispatch fires before the branch replicates): the ordering mitigation is CREATE feature branch -> confirm it is on the mirror -> THEN push story changes; the recheck ChatOps (comment 'recheck' -> g2p re-dispatch) is the fallback if the first dispatch loses the race. Will document this ordering + fallback in the dispatch note (and S4 contributor docs). My live evidence used this ordering (branch created, verified replicated, then pushed).\n- [G1G2/#13,#14] Deploy path: the committed infra/gerrit/replication.config is the source of truth; the canonical deploy is setup-replication.sh (copies to the site etc + the g2p bind-mount at /var/gerrit/site/g2p-config/ at compose-up). My live hot-edit of the gerrit_etc volume (autoReload) was expedient for evidence; will note that a full/clean deploy re-runs setup-replication.sh so the g2p copy is also refreshed (g2p reads replication.config only for REMOTE DISCOVERY, not push refspecs, so the stale g2p copy does NOT affect dispatch — but keep them in sync). Back-out AC will be added.\n\nDEFER w/ JUSTIFICATION (follow-up, NOT S3):\n- [E3/G1G2/#2,#3] Push-CI fan-out: test.yml/eval.yml/optionality.yml trigger on push:branches:['**'], so replicated feature/* pushes fan out 3 extra runs on the mirror. Justification for deferral: (a) it is CI NOISE/COST, not a correctness break — those runs cast NO Verified vote (gerrit-verify workflow_dispatch is the sole Verified source), so the two-vote gate is unaffected; (b) the fan-out is PRE-EXISTING for other replicated branches (feat/*, claude/* already on the mirror). Filing a follow-up ticket to scope feature/** out of those triggers. Modifying those workflows is outside S3's gated scope.\n- [T5c/T4/T9/#4,#6,#7] Mirror-side feature/* teardown (mirror=false won't prune deleted feature branches): owned by S6 (stale-branch inventory); will ensure S6 covers the GitHub-mirror side, and note a manual fallback.\n\nAC CLARITY (minor): #9 (define 'sanely' for concurrency as observable assertions), #11 (name the dispatch-note file), #12 (add back-out AC) — will tighten the ACs."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1783063046602496001,"uuid":"5a80a5d4-3918-40f5-8ace-f529646b3d12"}